*Requirements-

1. Install Oracle instant client 11.2
   Refrence: https://gist.github.com/kimus/10012910
   Refrence: http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/database/features/instant-client/index-097480.html
2. Install cx_Oracle
   Refrence: https://gist.github.com/kimus/10012910 

   
------------------------------------------------- Install Python3.5.2 -------------------------------------------------
1. Login as root user
2. mkdir /root/software/python
3. cd /root/software/python
4. wget https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.5.2/Python-3.5.2.tgz
5. tar -xvf Python-3.5.2.tgz
6. cd /root/software/python/Python-3.5.2
7. ./configure
8. make
9. make install
10. ls /usr/local/bin/ to check install python3.5

----------------------------- Change python version on per user basis -----------------------
1. cd
2. vim .bashrc
3. alias python='/usr/localh/bin/python3.5'

----------------------------- Change python version system-wide -----------------------
update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/python python /usr/bin/python2.6 1
update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/python python /usr/local/bin/python3.5 2
-- To set Priority
update-alternatives --config python
-- To remove
update-alternatives --remove python /usr/bin/python3.5

More Details :
1. https://linuxconfig.org/how-to-change-from-default-to-alternative-python-version-on-debian-linux
2. http://askubuntu.com/questions/701375/how-can-i-uninstall-python3-5-0-installed-from-source-code

------------------------------------------------- Install cx_Oracle -------------------------------------------------
1. Login as root user
2. mkdir /root/software/python
3. cd /root/software/python
4. wget https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.5.2/Python-3.5.2.tgz
5. tar -xvf Python-3.5.2.tgz
6. cd /root/software/python/Python-3.5.2
7. ./configure
8. make
9. make install
10. ls /usr/local/bin/ to check install python3.5
